  "text": "The effect of latrepirdine on A␤ aggregation was measured using the thioT amyloid-binding fluorescence assay. Fluorescence was measured using a FLUOStar Optima (BMG Labtech, Ortenberg, Germany), excitation and emission maxima were set to 450 nm and 490 nm respectively. The A␤ was prepared in the presence or absence of various concentrations of latrepirdine [CITATION_1] 50 , 100, and 200 M) and incubated with 5 M thioT for 16 h with fluorescence readings made at 10 min intervals. Experiments were performed in quadruplicate wells and each experiment was repeated a minimum of three times. Control background thioT fluorescence was subtracted from all sample results for each assay.",
